    "webdav_setup_guide": "<p class=\"mb-2\">The configuration depends on the WebDAV application you are using:</p>\n<div class=\"space-y-2 mb-2 pl-1.5 border-l-2 border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700\">\n  <div><span class=\"font-bold text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">1. Separate Port field (e.g., RaiDrive)</span></div>\n  <ul class=\"list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400\">\n    <li><span class=\"font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">Host:</span> Your IP/Domain (without http or port)</li>\n    <li><span class=\"font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">Port:</span> Enter the port number the web is running on</li>\n    <li><span class=\"font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">Path:</span> /webdav</li>\n    <li><span class=\"font-medium text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">Protocol:</span> HTTP (or HTTPS if you have SSL)</li>\n  </ul>\n  <div class=\"mt-2.5\"><span class=\"font-bold text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">2. Only 1 URL field (e.g., Windows Map Network Drive)</span></div>\n  <ul class=\"list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400\">\n    <li>Enter the full URL: <span class=\"font-mono bg-slate-200/50 dark:bg-slate-700/50 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300\">http(s)://[IP]:[Port]/webdav</span></li>\n  </ul>\n</div>\n<p class=\"text-[11px] italic opacity-80 mt-3 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 pt-2\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb text-amber-500 mr-1\"></i>Summary: If asked for a separate Port, separate it. If only asked for URL, combine port into URL.</p>",
